## Deletion

### Soft Delete (Default)

```
1. Mark file record as deleted (deletedAt timestamp)
2. Keep file in storage for retention period (30-90 days)
3. Cron job permanently deletes expired soft-deleted files
4. User sees "File deleted" - can be restored within retention period (optional)
```

### Hard Delete

```
When to hard delete:
  - User requests account deletion (GDPR right to erasure)
  - Compliance requirement
  - Storage cost optimization after retention period

Process:
  1. Delete from storage (all variants)
  2. Delete database record
  3. Delete from CDN cache (purge)
  4. Log deletion for audit trail
```

### Orphan Cleanup

```
Problem: Files uploaded but never attached (user started upload, didn't submit form)

Solution:
  - Upload to temp/ directory first
  - Move to permanent location when form is submitted
  - Cron job deletes temp files older than 24 hours
  - Track file status: temp -> attached -> deleted
```

