## Chunked Upload (Large Files)

For files over 10MB, use chunked upload:

```
1. Client requests upload session: POST /api/uploads/init { filename, totalSize, mimeType }
   -> Server returns { uploadId, chunkSize: 5MB }

2. Client splits file into chunks and uploads each:
   PUT /api/uploads/{uploadId}/chunks/{chunkNumber}
   -> Server stores chunk temporarily

3. Client signals completion: POST /api/uploads/{uploadId}/complete
   -> Server reassembles chunks, validates, processes

4. Server returns final file record

Benefits:
  - Resumable uploads (retry only failed chunks)
  - Progress tracking per chunk
  - Works on slow/unreliable connections
  - No timeout issues for large files
```

